Apple has been affected by the yo-yo effect.
It's all the displays.
A more powerful processor, a larger-resolution camera, a stronger chassis or a touch-sensitive display are in short the advantages of the recently introduced ninth-generation iPhones.
The last two also have a negative impact on the dimensions and weights of the iPhone 6s and 6s Plus.
Apple’s trend so far was that every new generation of iPhones is lighter than the previous one.
The only exceptions were the third and fourth generations, whose weight had slightly increased compared to the previous iPhones.
The two-gram weight difference to the disadvantage of the novelty was really negligible.
However, this is far from the case with the new iPhones.
Compared to last year's iPhone 6 and 6 Plus, the weight increased by 14 grams for the smaller model, and the larger one by a full 20 grams.
On the one hand, it is not surprising, last year's affair by bending in Apple's pockets greatly troubled.
The chassis of the novelties is thus made of more durable aluminum alloy 7000, which was also reflected in the weight.
But the displays have a much bigger impact on it.
Apple used 3D Touch technology for the new albums, thanks to which the displays recognize the power of touch.
To do this, it was necessary to provide the display with an additional layer of capacitive sensors.
The weight of the new iPhone displays has increased more than twice as many as previous generations.
For a smaller iPhone from originally 12 grams to 29 grams, in the case of a larger one, then from 19 to 40 grams.
For the iPhone 6s, the display is the heaviest component used.
The weight of only 143 grams is then achieved with this novelty thanks to the slimming bark, which touched most of the remaining components.
For a larger model, the battery is the heaviest element used, but its weight has not changed compared to its predecessor.
Even in this case, the biggest increase is evident in the display.
The weight of the 5.5" iPhone 6s Plus thus reaches 192 grams.
The extent to which the new display technology will be practical will be felt only when used.
First users will be able to try it as early as Friday, September 25, when the sale of iPhone 6s and 6s Plus will start in selected countries.
