Chinese President Xi Jinping will visit the U.S. at the end of the month, the White House confirmed in its report on Tuesday.
President Xi's first visit to Washington will take place on September 25 in a response from Barack Obama to visit Beijing, where the president visited in November, the report said.
U.S. President and First Lady Michelle Obama invite President Xi and his wife, Peng Liyuan, to a state dinner to be held after the talks.
