Insurance companies should pay clients’ claims in the event of bankruptcy of the travel agency in full.
This was decided by the Chamber of Deputies on Wednesday when it approved a revised amendment to the Act on the Conditions of Business in Tourism.
Travel agencies will be able to replace insurance against bankruptcy with a bank guarantee, according to the draft heading to the Senate.
Insurance companies do not agree with the obligation to pay the claims of clients even above the agreed limit.
The Ministry of Regional Development insists on the regulation, argues consumer protection.
Insurance companies have already threatened to terminate the insurance of travel agencies against bankruptcy when the amendment applies.
