One of the options for travel agencies can cope with such a situation will be a lawsuit against the state for compensation.
Another option will be to go abroad and use much softer conditions abroad, and in our market we will then act only as agencies, said the vice-chairman of the association, Jan Papež, the association's vice-president.
According to him, the draft amendment also contains the institute of a bank guarantee, but so unpremeditated that it cannot be implemented in practice at all, because the bank guarantee cannot sound at an unbounded amount.
Moreover, according to the association, the change in the current practice is de facto unnecessary.
Within two years, it will be necessary to recast the whole law again in the light of the new EU directive.
A total of 942 active insured travel agencies are now operating on the Czech market.
This year, only three CKs have ceased their activities.
Domestic travel agencies sell tours worth about twenty billion CZK annually.
